HEADWORD: Deckle edge
<hw>Dec"kle edge`</hw>. <def>The rough, untrimmed edge of paper left by
the deckle; also, a rough edge in imitation of this.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deckled</ent>⟦br⟧
